    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="461"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Paper</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">List of Amendments to the Draft Communiqué</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d461fn1">Authorship not indicated.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Yalta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-11">February 11,
                            1945</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Prime Minister’s Amendments to Draft Communiqué</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">Defeat of Germany</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="underline">Line 8:</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">For</hi>“co-ordination”</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="underline">Read:</hi> “concert”</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="underline">Line 9:</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">After</hi> “launched”</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="underline">Insert:</hi> “continuously”.</p>
                <p>Three lines lower down, <hi rend="underline">instead</hi> of “our joint military
                    plans”, <hi rend="underline">read</hi> “our combined military plans”.</p>
                <p>The word “joint” appears twice in the next three lines, and the Prime Minister
                    would omit it in these two places.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Occupation and Control of Germany</hi>
                </p>
                <p>In the second line <hi rend="underline">for</hi> the word “jointly” <hi
                        rend="underline">substitute</hi> the word “together”.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="underline">Line 7</hi>—the word “co-ordinated” should be struck out
                    and “united” substituted.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="underline">Line 10</hi>—the last sentence of the paragraph should read
                    as follows:—</p>
                <pb facs="1026" n="930" xml:id="pg_930"/>
                <p>“It has been agreed that France should be invited by the Three Powers if she
                    should so desire to take over a fourth zone of occupation, and to participate as
                    a fourth member of the Control Commission.”</p>
                <p>In the first line of the next paragraph <hi rend="underline">for</hi> “it is our
                    joint purpose” <hi rend="underline">read</hi> “It is our inflexible
                    purpose”.</p>
                <p>In the third line of this paragraph <hi rend="underline">for</hi> “threaten” <hi
                        rend="underline">read</hi> “disturb”.</p>
                <p>Six lines from the bottom of the paragraph, <hi rend="underline">instead of</hi>
                    “to take jointly such other measures” <hi rend="underline">read</hi> “to take in
                    harmony such other measures”.</p>
                <p>The last sentence of the paragraph on this page should read as follows:—</p>
                <p>“It is not our purpose to destroy the people of Germany, but only when Nazism and
                    Militarism have been extirpated will there be hope for a decent life for the
                    Germans and a place for them in the comity of nations”.</p>
            </div>
